title: Scharf, No. 5 'Dogs Knock Off No. 20 Vikings
text:
Scharf, No. 5 'Dogs Knock Off No. 20 Vikings 
By Zach Schneider October 16, 2015 Updated Oct 16, 2015 at 9:55 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Mariah Scharf finished with a match-high 21 kills on Friday night as the No. 5 University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) volleyball team knocked off No. 20 Augustana 3-1 at Romano Gymnasium. 
Sarah Kelly finished with 15 kills for UMD, and Monica Turner added 12 kills in the winning effort. Erin Schindler was the defensive leader with 26 digs, while Ashley Hinsch had 57 set assists.
